  "description": "Survey of feminist organizational theory from Acker, Calás and Smircich, Martin, Federici, and hooks—examining how governance structures are gendered, how formal neutrality reproduces power asymmetries, how invisible labor subsidizes governance, and why theory itself must center those marginalized by organizational structures.",
  "name": "Feminist Organizational Theory: A Survey of How Governance Reproduces Gender Inequality",
